        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Nov 17. 1871</date>
                    <salute>Dear Professor Oliver</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>You have been very kind to take so much trouble for me; the information is amply sufficient, as I wished to learn how far the roots c<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> act on rocks, not caring about the nutrition of the plants.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>Yours truly obliged | Ch Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">CD had asked Oliver whether it was believed that rootlets secreted carbonic acid or similar chemicals (<ref target="./DCP-LETT-8068.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to Daniel Oliver, 15 November 1871</ref>). Oliver’s reply has not been found.</note>
        </div>        
            
